  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "*Description*:\r\nIf you configure load balancing to use this source IP:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"hash_policy\": [\r\n    {\r\n        \"connection_properties\": {\r\n            \"source_ip\": true\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/8b4c2d6119a5163d4f781b57a5b14b7130ddc2a2/source/common/router/router.h#L156 the remote IP plus the port is used, that makes it not work (for my use case)  with each new connection opened by a client from the same host. \r\n\r\nI believe it either needs to be documented or changed to behave like the \"DOWNSTREAM_REMOTE_ADDRESS_WITHOUT_PORT\" access log token.\r\n\r\nMore info:\r\nhttps://groups.google.com/forum/?utm_medium=email&utm_source=footer#!msg/envoy-users/PAA8tXZnbA0/hU870nSuCAAJ\r\n",
